Subject: [PATCH 0/2] media: synopsys: hdmirx: add HDMI RX audio capture

Adds HDMI-input audio capture to the mainline synopsys-hdmirx driver
(RK3588). Registers the generic hdmi-codec so a simple-audio-card binds
the HDMI RX audio DAI; recovers the sample rate from ACR N/CTS; a periodic
worker locks the audio clock to the source to avoid FIFO drift and dropped
samples. Tested on an Orange Pi 5 Plus capturing 44.1/48 kHz stereo.

Igor-rk3588 (2):
  dt-bindings: media: snps,dw-hdmi-rx: add #sound-dai-cells
  media: synopsys: hdmirx: add HDMI audio capture support

